The adsorption/desorption isotherms and the BJH plot of the PbTiO3 and PbTiO3/5% CQDs samples (Fig. 6
                     a–d) indicate the pore volume and surface area of the samples. Fig. 6b reflects a broad pore size distribution with a maximum of about 26 nm in diameter. The total pore volume and average pore diameter of the sample were 0.07164 cm3/g and 21.31 nm. Additionally the BET specific surface area of the sample was 37.33 m2/g. It was also found that surface of the PbTiO3/5% CQDs samples prepared increased while its size decreased (Fig. 6c). According to the IUPAC classifications, the N2 adsorption/desorption isotherm is a type IV isotherm with H1-type hysteresis loops, which is an important feature of ordered mesophorous materials. Fig. 6d illustrates the pore size distribution of the PbTiO3/CQDs binary nano-hybrid, indicating a broad pore size distribution with a maximum pore diameter of 25 nm. The overall volume and mean diameter of the pores, as well as the BET specific surface area of the sample were around 0.1454 cm3/g and 19.53 nm, and 60.49 m2/g respectively. (Table 2
                     ).
